<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-03-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-03-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="143" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">832.24/1401: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-24">March 24, 1943</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1072. Your airgram A–415, March 6;<note n="58" xml:id="d143fn1">Not
                                    printed; it indicated that export controls from the United
                                    States to Brazil would be decentralized so that the Carteira de
                                    Exportação e Importação of the Bank of Brazil would make the
                                    recommendations on export preference requests upon proof that
                                    orders had been accepted by American firms (832.24/1384).</note>
                                and telegram 1347, March 18, 1943.<note n="59" xml:id="d143fn2">Not
                                    printed.</note> Board of Economic Warfare concurs in final draft
                                of memorandum.<note n="59" xml:id="d143fn3">Not printed.</note> You
                                may formalize this agreement by an exchange of notes with the
                                Ministry of Foreign Affairs.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>